    <string name="settings_data_sources">Market data sources</string>
    <string name="settings_data_sources_body">Choose quote, chart-data, and valuation providers independently. Vico renders charts inside the app; the chart-data provider supplies historical OHLCV. Each choice is stored only on this device.</string>
    <string name="settings_quote_provider">Live quotes</string>
    <string name="settings_chart_provider">Historical chart data</string>
    <string name="settings_chart_provider_explanation">Why is an external source needed? Candlesticks require a history of open, high, low, close, and volume values; a current quote is not enough. Vico only draws those records locally and does not provide market data. Tencent and Sina are used here for quote snapshots, but their US historical-bar interfaces were not reliable enough to activate. This serverless app therefore needs a separate data source for chart history. Alpaca Live IEX is the current optional BYOK source; leaving it unconfigured disables historical charts.</string>
